channel.display-name: The Bob Ross Channel en Espanol

programme.title: Everybody Loves a Moose
programme.desc: An oddball buddy series between an over ambitious boy, Jack and his pal Moose, a melodramatic self-confessed expert in everything. Except he isn't! Despite his best intentions, he always messes up and although Jack may not get what he want, you can't help being sucked in by Moose's relentless optimism and zest for life!

programme.title: Princess Play Time
programme.desc: The proud Princess likes to do things her own way, but her antics are always joined by her restless brother, Prince, who tends to turn everything topsy-turvy. Any playtime in their room transforms into a fantastic journey through unusual worlds: the children arrange a picnic on the Moon, conduct a detective investigation in a toy city, or search for pirate treasures on islands! Although initially, the Princess and Prince seem to clash and compete, by the end, they always find joy in each other's company and that of their cherished dog, Bona.

programme.title: Om Nom Stories
programme.desc: Sweet tooth Om Nom is wandering Around the world, eats a lot of candies and tries to find his Dream job. Watch his adventures and solve different puzzles on the way!

programme.title: Box Yourself
programme.desc: Great Projects From Ordinary Cardboard!

programme.title: Ollie! The Boy Who Became What He Ate
programme.desc: Ollie is a 6-year-old with a massive imagination, often lost in his own world - flipping, sliding, climbing and rocket-blasting through the house, practicing at being the master of all things. But even masters need to stop and refuel. When meals or snack time interrupt Ollie’s play, he finds himself confronted with the real challenge of childhood; trying new food. To escape his predicament, Ollie uses his magic spoon to transport himself, along with his sister Poppy, and her stuffy Nummy, to a food planet filled with adventure and the very food Ollie stuck his spoon into.

programme.title: Sunny Bunnies
programme.desc: The Sunny Bunnies are five fluffy balls of light named Turbo, Big Boo, Shiny, Iris and Hopper who can appear anywhere there is light. The Bunnies always bring joy and happiness, beaming down to explore new and exciting locations, finding fun and mischievous games to enjoy.

programme.title: Cyboars
programme.desc: Part Machine, Part Boar, All Hero!

programme.title: Box Yourself
programme.desc: Great Projects From Ordinary Cardboard!

programme.title: The Drain
programme.desc: Tom Thomas accidently drops his mom's wedding ring down the drain and thinks it is gone forever until Simka and Nolik help him retrieve the ring from the drain trap with the help of a pack-o-mat.

programme.title: The DVD
programme.desc: Tom Thomas has to return a DVD he borrowed from his friend but discovers his player can't read the disk anymore. Simka and Nolik help Tom Thomas clean it so it works again.

programme.title: GREEN ATTACK
programme.desc: Pam is worried because she still hasn't found out which is her talent that will enable her to become a PopPixie. As Ninfea and her friends encourages her, a carnivorous plant invades Pixieville.

programme.title: Teamwork of the People: Part 1 of 5
programme.desc: Michael jumps for joy. He is holding the DVD of "CAPTAIN MUSCLES 2" which they are going to watch it tonight in Neverland!

programme.title: Teamwork of the People: Part 2 of 5
programme.desc: When Synapse threatens to spray Captain Muscles with a serum that will exacerbate his faults, Sienna, caught up in the film, falls and causes a magical short-circuit.

programme.title: Teamwork of the People: Part 3 of 5
programme.desc: The potion and Captain Muscles cross through the screen. Hit by the serum, Sienna writhes around and then flees into the forest, growling.

programme.title: Teamwork of the People: Part 4 of 5
programme.desc: Captain Muscles and Peter Pan are immediately ready for action because John explains that they need to find a way to stop Sienna before he grows and crushes all of Neverland!

programme.title: Grojband
programme.desc: The story about 12 year old Corey that emotionally torments his sister so that she will write the ultimate lyrics for his garage band.

programme.title: Pumpkin Reports
programme.desc: Max Green’s new brother and sister are aliens sent to Earth as the advance party for an invasion - and he’s the only one who can stop them turning humans into unwilling slave-gardeners.

programme.title: I'll Get You! Holiday
programme.desc: The action takes place in all year round resort, where Wolf doesn't chase Hare to eat him anymore: now it's all about sports and competition. However, in his crazy chase after recognition and victories the grey hooligan often uses methods that aren't really fair, which provokes awkward and funny situations.

programme.title: Pirate school
programme.desc: On a small remote island surrounded by endless seas, a special Pirate School was opened, where children from pirate families study. Among them are Keel, Fuse and Bobo. The pirate origin does not relieve them from study and normal school duties.

programme.title: Sunny Bunnies
programme.desc: The Sunny Bunnies are five fluffy balls of light named Turbo, Big Boo, Shiny, Iris and Hopper who can appear anywhere there is light. The Bunnies always bring joy and happiness, beaming down to explore new and exciting locations, finding fun and mischievous games to enjoy.

programme.title: VIP Pets
programme.desc: We are the VIP Pets! The coolest pets with a passion for hair! We are best friends and together we will discover lots of beautiful hairstyles and go on exciting adventures!

programme.title: The Secrets of Honey Hills
programme.desc: Honey Hills is a small seaside town where all kind of animals live. It's a good neighbourhood. However, mysterious and inexplicable events sometimes cause misunderstandings among neighbours. Then, genius detective Sophie the Owl together with her young assistant Chirp the Squirrel take up the investigation.

programme.title: The Adventures of Peter and Wolf
programme.desc: A sitcom about the adventures of ordinary schoolboy Peter and talking Wolf connecting the world of people to parallel universes, where there live robots and vampires, werewolves and zombies, giants and aliens, fairies and centaurs, clones and invisible men! The characters will have to solve locals' problems and regularly save the world.

programme.title: The Fixies
programme.desc: The Fixies follows the comical misadventures of Tom Thomas and his secret friendship with Simka and Nolik, the children of the Fixie family that lives in his apartment. There’s just no end to the troubles Tom Thomas and his Fixie friends get themselves into with all the gadgets and appliances around them!

programme.title: Eliot Kid
programme.desc: When a tooth falling out turns into a hunt for the “giant mouse”, when the city’s sewers transform into Indiana Jones’ white rapids or when a trip to the toilets becomes an expedition to a haunted house, well then you’ve entered the wonderful world of Eliot Kid!

programme.title: Angry Birds Toons
programme.desc: Check out Angry Birds Toons compilations! Each compilation has several episodes from your favorite shows including Angry Birds, Piggy Tales, and Stella!

programme.title: Chefclub Kids
programme.desc: With Chefclub Kids, the little ones get their hands dirty all while having fun in the kitchen. Whether they're learning to prepare dinner, bake goodies, or explore new flavors, Chefclub Kids is a way for children to gain confidence through cooking!

programme.title: GWR Incredible Record Breakers
programme.desc: Guinness World Records presents Incredible Record Breakers from all over.

programme.title: Episodio 8
programme.desc: Laura es una bella joven heredera de una millonaria fortuna. Sin embargo, todo ese dinero no le ha causado mas que dolores de cabeza y al corazon, mientras espera encontrar algun dia el verdadero amor. Lamentablemente para Laura, el hombre que ahora intenta ganarse su corazon es una sanguijuela. Todo lo que busca es su dinero y la seguridad financiera que puede darle. Su sueno siempre ha sido encontrar a una rica y bella heredera y Laura es la chica que escoge como blanco. Al mismo tiempo, este hombre tiene un romance con la salvaje y peligrosa prima de Laura, por la que siente una ardiente pasion.

programme.title: Episodio 60
programme.desc: Paula C. es la muchacha mas popular del barrio Republica. Posee un angel que la hace inolvidable y encantadora. Por eso, el dia que Diego Lujan, el joven empresario y futuro heredero de un imperio de cosmeticos, se cruzo con ella, se le marcaron sus ojos para siempre en la memoria. Diego estaba a una semana de casarse con la modelo mas hermosa de la ciudad: Vicky Cardenas. Ella era la imagen exclusiva de las empresas Avila y la afortunada prometida de un soltero impenitente y codiciado, como siempre se le habia conocido a Diego. Pero el destino jugo sus cartas. El encuentro entre Paula C. y Diego fue lo mas parecido a una tormenta, o lo que es lo mismo, a una gran historia de amor. Porque a Paula C. le paso exactamente lo mismo cuando vio a Diego: el estremecimiento de un huracan.

programme.title: Episodio 111
programme.desc: Adolfo planea sacar a Natalia de Playa Esperanza y la sedan y luego se la lleva Pirana. Natalia despierta y toma la pistola de Pirana y le dice que la lleve a Mar Encantado pero en el trayecto aparece Irene y toma por detras a Natalia y con todo esto se produce un accidente y la cami8oneta cae en el rio y no se sabe nada del paradero de sus ocupantes. Valerio le dice a Adolfo que el es el padre de Natalia y que esta es su hija con Paulina, Adolfo se enfurece y entonces comienza una gresca entre ambos y se dan varios y severos golpes. Rosarito sale de su operacion positivamente ya q1ue puede ver pero todavia le falta ver a Gerardo. Jacinto le confiesa a Gerardo que sabe lo que le paso a Rosarito pero cree que no debe contarlo aunque Gerardo le pide que le diga de que se trata.

programme.title: Episodio 112
programme.desc: Mientras toda la gente del pueblo se entera del accidente que involucra a Natalia, Pirana, e Irene, y las familias lloran la posible muerte de Natalia e Irene, Sara, Julian y Perla celebran esas muertes, especialmente la de Natalia. Viviana aprovecha para acercarse a Adolfo y consolarlo. Tambien le pide que la deje mudarse a la mansion Uzcategui, para asi tener a su hijo ahi y dejarlo que Adolfo lo crie a su manera. Adolfo se siente debil al momento y acepta, en tanto no encuentren a Natalia. Luis Manuel regresa de Miami y se encuentra con Perla en el hotel, quien le da la noticia de la desaparicion de Natalia, y ahi mismo se va para confrontar a Adolfo y culparlo de querer llevarsela de Playa Esperanza.

programme.title: Episodio 113
programme.desc: Luis Manuel le pregunta a Pirana que paso con Natalia pero el no sabe nada porque se desmayo y cuando desperto ya no habia nadie. Entonces todos piensan que Natalia e Irene se murieron ahogadas, pero como no encuentran los cuerpos, algunos tienen esperanzas de que esten vivas. Mas tarde Luis Manuel y Adolfo se cruzan en la taguara de Pasionaria y se enfrentan, discuten un rato y por ultimo Adolfo le confiesa que prefiere que su mujer se haya muerto antes de verla en sus brazos. Por otro lado Vivianita le cuenta a Pasionaria que manana se va a mudar a la mansion Uzcategui, entonces esta le pide ayuda para que se robe el cofre lleno de joyas. Irene y Natalia son encontradas y llevadas para el rancho de la vieja Tirsa,

programme.title: Episodio 114
programme.desc: Tirsa le da unas hierbas a Natalia y al rato esta reacciona pero ha perdido la memoria, no se acuerda de nada. Rosarito siente la voz de Julian y lo reconoce, entonces lo echa de su casa pero el la atormenta y le quiere hacer dano. Luego aparecen Jacinto y Pastora y lo echan de la casa. Vivianita entra a la habitacion de Sara, le usa sus perfumes y tambien encuentra el cofre con las joyas que piensa robarselo. Luego entra Sara y la ve, entonces se golpean durisimo hasta que Adolfo las separa. Gerardo y Vanesa se conocen y acuerdan para que el la lleve a conocer el pueblo. Perla se reune con Luis Manuel y le pide una segunda oportunidad pero el no se puede olvidar tan facilmente de Natalia, ya que esperaba un hijo suyo.

programme.title: Episodio 115
programme.desc: Luis Manuel habla con Perla y le dice que no la quiere ver, que lo deje en paz y que quiere estar solo. Patricia llega con Diego a Playa Esperanza y piensa su plan para separar a Bruno de Candy. Natalia sigue sin poder recordar nada e Irene se le rie porque piensa que se esta volviendo loca como ella. Diego no aguanta estar encerrado y sale a dar una vuelta a la playa. Entonces se encuentra a Pasionaria que lo nota raro pero lo confunde con Bruno. Ellos conversan un rato y finalmente el termina besandola dejandola sorprendida. Por otro lado Candy y Bruno vuelven de su luna de miel y se enteran de la desaparicion de Natalia e Irene.

programme.title: Episodio 16
programme.desc: Antonio le pide ruega a su padre que no le quite los autos que le regalo a sus hijas y el acepta su disculpa. Luego Gregorio le pide a Valentin que vigile a Antonio para que no descubra que falsifico el testamento de su madre para quedarse con todo. Mas tarde se encuentra con Doris y le promete que la va a proteger para que no se separe de Antonio pero Doris quiere tener poder sobre Gregorio y le pide a Brigitte que arregle una cita con Gregorio para poder seducirlo. Elvira piensa intercambiar las pastillas para el corazon de Gregorio por veneno para ratas. Luego recibe una orden de Antonio para convencer a Camila de que Pedro se va a encontrar con su esposa en el aeropuerto.

programme.title: Episodio 17
programme.desc: Pedro cae en la trampa preparada por Antonio y Lucrecia, y Camila se entera alli que Pedro le ha mentido sobre su esposa, y que ademas Lucrecia es su amante. Antonio llega para consolarla, y Pedro no logra explicarle nada. Camila se siente muy dolida por la mentira de Pedro y habla con Tracy, pero Tracy la convence de que la han enganado, y la lleva a la comisaria para certificar que Mariana, la esposa de Pedro, sigue perdida. Por otro lado, Pedro visita Lucrecia en El Alcatraz, y le pide explicaciones. Lucrecia logra evadirse de culpa y parecer inocente, echandole toda la culpa del engano a Antonio, y asi seguir permaneciendo del lado de Pedro. - Doris ve a Pedro y Lucrecia charlando y le avisa inmediatamente a Gregorio.

programme.title: Episodio 18
programme.desc: Pedro es descubierto por Gregorio en sus tierras, por lo que este ultimo decide ir a matarlo, pero Lucrecia logra evitar que lo haga. - Cuando el senor Ibarra llega a su casa descubre que Camila estaba ahi. Esperandolo para pedirles disculpas. Sin mas vueltas, el la perdona y comienzan a estar juntos nuevamente. Al poco tiempo Lucrecia se entera de esto y decide que la mejor manera de lograr que Pedro este con ella es dandole lastima. Con ese proposito le dice a Antonio que Camila sabe que fue el quien contrato a Julia para que se hiciera pasar por la esposa de Pedro, y de esa manera logro que su hermano la golpeara sin piedad. Su intencion es decirle a su amado que fue Gregorio quien la golpeo.

programme.title: Episodio 19
programme.desc: Camila y Pedro ya formalizaron su relacion, ella por cuestiones de trabajo va a vivir en El Talisman, pero por temor a los chismes (dado que Pedro sigue casado) decide vivir en las cabanas del rancho y no en la casa principal. Sin demorase mucho, le informo de esto a su madre y a su hermano. La primera intento de todas formas hacerle ver que estaba cometiendo un error, pero no lo consiguio. Y en el interin, Armando aprovecho para contarle a Camila que Elvira estaba saliendo con un millonario. Esto la dejo muy preocupada, y no solo eso, sino tambien el hecho de que si bien su hermano es muy bueno, teme que este pueda ser influenciado por su madre para vengarse de Gregorio.

programme.title: Episodio 20
programme.desc: Lucrecia llega a El Talisman toda golpeada y Pedro la recibe y la atiende un medico. Para evitar futuros problemas con Camila, decide ir a contarle lo que esta pasando, pero ella se enoja y amenaza con irse de la hacienda si Lucrecia no se va. Desconfia de que la golpiza recibida sea cierta y decide verla con sus propios ojos. Cuando va, se da cuenta que Lucrecia no esta tan mal como pensaba y que todo es parte de la estrategia para conquistar a Pedro. Lucrecia insiste con que su padre la ha golpeado salvajemente y que necesita que Pedro la hospede. Camila la obliga a marcharse y llama a Antonio para que venga a buscarla. Como el muchacho quiere conquistar a Camila, va en busca de su hermana y al llegar, se la lleva al hospital.

programme.title: Episodio 60
programme.desc: Paula C. es la muchacha mas popular del barrio Republica. Posee un angel que la hace inolvidable y encantadora. Por eso, el dia que Diego Lujan, el joven empresario y futuro heredero de un imperio de cosmeticos, se cruzo con ella, se le marcaron sus ojos para siempre en la memoria. Diego estaba a una semana de casarse con la modelo mas hermosa de la ciudad: Vicky Cardenas. Ella era la imagen exclusiva de las empresas Avila y la afortunada prometida de un soltero impenitente y codiciado, como siempre se le habia conocido a Diego. Pero el destino jugo sus cartas. El encuentro entre Paula C. y Diego fue lo mas parecido a una tormenta, o lo que es lo mismo, a una gran historia de amor. Porque a Paula C. le paso exactamente lo mismo cuando vio a Diego: el estremecimiento de un huracan.

programme.title: Episodio 6
programme.desc: El doctor Santiago decide retirar la denuncia contra Micaela, ya que considera que era injusto porque no habia pruebas en su contra y que la justicia se encargara de resolver el caso. Cuando Santiago le conto a Gala, lo que habia hecho, ella se enojo mucho, porque para Gala, Micaela era culpable. Y ademas, cuando Karla y Daniel, socios de la clinica de Santiago, se enteraron no lo podian creer. Lucia recibe la inesperada llamada de Guillermo; luego de una pequena conversacion acuerdan encontrarse al dia siguiente. La madre de Lucia, Maruja, no pudo dejar de notar la sonrisa dibujada en su rostro. Carla discute con Larry porque se llevo a la nina sin autorizacion.

programme.title: Episodio 7
programme.desc: El Nene, luego de desviar a Sanchez que estaba buscando a Micaela, va corriendo a la casa para avisarle a ella lo que habia sucedido y la ayuda a escapar. Larry va ver a Karla al centro estetico para decirle que no puede olvidarse de ella y para pedirle otra oportunidad, sin embargo Karla no se deja convencer. Estrella se encuentra con Saturno para devolverle el panuelo que le habia prestado y en ese instante aparece Nella la madre de Gala, quien los ve y les llama la atencion. Gala y Rogelio siguen discutiendo por el “capricho” de Gala de no hacer el personaje que le asignaron ya ella argumenta que es una figura y que sus novelas son un exito por ella.

programme.title: Episodio 8
programme.desc: Santiago investiga a Micaela con el fin de entenderla mas a fondo, mientras que ella describe sus problemas y confiesa que dice cosas que a la gente no le gusta escuchar, por tal razon, la mayoria de las veces la evitan dejandola de lado. Maruja charla sobre su casa y sin pensar termina hablando de su vida sentimental. Nella, quien escucha a su amiga, le dice que tiene que dar otro rumbo a su vida ya que se encuentra muy sola, que otra seria la historia si hubiese aceptado el amor de Guillermo Toro. Nene, ilusionado con la cita con el empresario, busca la mejor ropa para impresionar y lo logra, por lo menos a Eva quien lo ve tan bien vestido. Lamentablemente el doctor Polanco tiene muy malas intenciones y esta decidido a llevar su perverso plan.

programme.title: Episodio 9
programme.desc: Santiago insiste en denunciar lo que Micaela le acaba de contar pero ella le dice que ya lo intento pero no pudo; de todas formas el insiste, pidiendole mucha prudencia, pues el policia la conoce, a su vez le pregunta si va a regresar al trabajo, ella le contesta que lo va a consultar con Ronaldinho. La premier de esta noche sera un evento al cual todo mundo ira, y desde muy temprano los invitados se preparan para estar presentes en el maravilloso evento. Micaela pasea tranquilamente por la ciudad, cuando de repente ve al policia corrupto que asalto la clinica, rapidamente huye del lugar, este corre tras ella, esquivando el transito, hasta que finalmente la sorprende en un callejon.

programme.title: Episodio 10
programme.desc: Guillermo se retira de la sala para refrescarse en el bano, porque se siente mareado, pero el agua no logra reanimarlo y se desvanece; Lucho lo asiste, pero el doctor se reincorpora y le insiste a Lucho que no hacia falta llamar a un doctor. Santiago se deslumbra al ver a Micaela subir por las escaleras y boquiabierto le dice lo bella que estaba. A cada momento no pierde la oportunidad de alagar a la muchacha, cuando ella trata de retirarse el la detiene y le pregunta si va a volver al trabajo a lo que ella responde afirmativamente. Larry llega apurado al restaurante y pregunta por su familia, le dicen que ya se retiraron y el se lamenta.

programme.title: Episodio 4
programme.desc: Laura es una bella joven heredera de una millonaria fortuna. Sin embargo, todo ese dinero no le ha causado mas que dolores de cabeza y al corazon, mientras espera encontrar algun dia el verdadero amor. Lamentablemente para Laura, el hombre que ahora intenta ganarse su corazon es una sanguijuela. Todo lo que busca es su dinero y la seguridad financiera que puede darle. Su sueno siempre ha sido encontrar a una rica y bella heredera y Laura es la chica que escoge como blanco. Al mismo tiempo, este hombre tiene un romance con la salvaje y peligrosa prima de Laura, por la que siente una ardiente pasion.

programme.title: Episodio 114
programme.desc: Esta magistral historia narra los hechos que marcaron la vida de Ines Duarte, una joven secretaria a quien la sobreproteccion maternal convirtio en un ser reprimido, en una persona gris, en una desconocedora total de su potencial como mujer. Ines Duarte es una secretaria eficiente, muy util, muy fiel, muy trabajadora. Ella es la sombra de un gran magnate, Andres Martan. Ines lo resuelve todo, ella es casi necesaria para su jefe. El y su trabajo son la razon de su vida. Poco a poco, la pasion va haciendose mas presente en el corazon de Ines, colmandolo del mas fiel y secreto amor. Pero la vida de Andres va por otros caminos, para el, Ines es poco mas que un robot programado para servirle. Un matrimonio, hijos, viudez y mucha amargura van conformando el cuadro de la vida de Andres Martan, convirtiendolo en un hombre duro, encerrado en si mismo, en un despota. Pero los grandes cambios vendran, una nueva Ines irrumpira en la trama dando un vuelco total a los acontecimientos, creando multiples e inesperadas situaciones que sorprenderan y atraparan al televidente en las redes de esta formidable novela.

Un matrimonio, hijos, viudez y mucha amargura van conformando el cuadro de la vida de Andres Martan, convirtiendolo en un hombre duro, encerrado en si mismo, en un despota. Pero los grandes cambios vendran, una nueva Ines irrumpira en la trama dando un vuelco total a los acontecimientos, creando multiples e inesperadas situaciones que sorprenderan y atraparan al televidente en las redes de esta formidable novela.

programme.title: Episodio 10
programme.desc: Guillermo se retira de la sala para refrescarse en el bano, porque se siente mareado, pero el agua no logra reanimarlo y se desvanece; Lucho lo asiste, pero el doctor se reincorpora y le insiste a Lucho que no hacia falta llamar a un doctor. Santiago se deslumbra al ver a Micaela subir por las escaleras y boquiabierto le dice lo bella que estaba. A cada momento no pierde la oportunidad de alagar a la muchacha, cuando ella trata de retirarse el la detiene y le pregunta si va a volver al trabajo a lo que ella responde afirmativamente. Larry llega apurado al restaurante y pregunta por su familia, le dicen que ya se retiraron y el se lamenta.

programme.title: Episodio 115
programme.desc: Luis Manuel habla con Perla y le dice que no la quiere ver, que lo deje en paz y que quiere estar solo. Patricia llega con Diego a Playa Esperanza y piensa su plan para separar a Bruno de Candy. Natalia sigue sin poder recordar nada e Irene se le rie porque piensa que se esta volviendo loca como ella. Diego no aguanta estar encerrado y sale a dar una vuelta a la playa. Entonces se encuentra a Pasionaria que lo nota raro pero lo confunde con Bruno. Ellos conversan un rato y finalmente el termina besandola dejandola sorprendida. Por otro lado Candy y Bruno vuelven de su luna de miel y se enteran de la desaparicion de Natalia e Irene.

programme.title: Episodio 20
programme.desc: Lucrecia llega a El Talisman toda golpeada y Pedro la recibe y la atiende un medico. Para evitar futuros problemas con Camila, decide ir a contarle lo que esta pasando, pero ella se enoja y amenaza con irse de la hacienda si Lucrecia no se va. Desconfia de que la golpiza recibida sea cierta y decide verla con sus propios ojos. Cuando va, se da cuenta que Lucrecia no esta tan mal como pensaba y que todo es parte de la estrategia para conquistar a Pedro. Lucrecia insiste con que su padre la ha golpeado salvajemente y que necesita que Pedro la hospede. Camila la obliga a marcharse y llama a Antonio para que venga a buscarla. Como el muchacho quiere conquistar a Camila, va en busca de su hermana y al llegar, se la lleva al hospital.

programme.title: Episodio 64
programme.desc: Paula C. es la muchacha mas popular del barrio Republica. Posee un angel que la hace inolvidable y encantadora. Por eso, el dia que Diego Lujan, el joven empresario y futuro heredero de un imperio de cosmeticos, se cruzo con ella, se le marcaron sus ojos para siempre en la memoria. Diego estaba a una semana de casarse con la modelo mas hermosa de la ciudad: Vicky Cardenas. Ella era la imagen exclusiva de las empresas Avila y la afortunada prometida de un soltero impenitente y codiciado, como siempre se le habia conocido a Diego. Pero el destino jugo sus cartas. El encuentro entre Paula C. y Diego fue lo mas parecido a una tormenta, o lo que es lo mismo, a una gran historia de amor. Porque a Paula C. le paso exactamente lo mismo cuando vio a Diego: el estremecimiento de un huracan.

programme.title: Episodio 8
programme.desc: Laura es una bella joven heredera de una millonaria fortuna. Sin embargo, todo ese dinero no le ha causado mas que dolores de cabeza y al corazon, mientras espera encontrar algun dia el verdadero amor. Lamentablemente para Laura, el hombre que ahora intenta ganarse su corazon es una sanguijuela. Todo lo que busca es su dinero y la seguridad financiera que puede darle. Su sueno siempre ha sido encontrar a una rica y bella heredera y Laura es la chica que escoge como blanco. Al mismo tiempo, este hombre tiene un romance con la salvaje y peligrosa prima de Laura, por la que siente una ardiente pasion.

programme.title: Episodio 118
programme.desc: Esta magistral historia narra los hechos que marcaron la vida de Ines Duarte, una joven secretaria a quien la sobreproteccion maternal convirtio en un ser reprimido, en una persona gris, en una desconocedora total de su potencial como mujer. Ines Duarte es una secretaria eficiente, muy util, muy fiel, muy trabajadora. Ella es la sombra de un gran magnate, Andres Martan. Ines lo resuelve todo, ella es casi necesaria para su jefe. El y su trabajo son la razon de su vida. Poco a poco, la pasion va haciendose mas presente en el corazon de Ines, colmandolo del mas fiel y secreto amor. Pero la vida de Andres va por otros caminos, para el, Ines es poco mas que un robot programado para servirle. Un matrimonio, hijos, viudez y mucha amargura van conformando el cuadro de la vida de Andres Martan, convirtiendolo en un hombre duro, encerrado en si mismo, en un despota. Pero los grandes cambios vendran, una nueva Ines irrumpira en la trama dando un vuelco total a los acontecimientos, creando multiples e inesperadas situaciones que sorprenderan y atraparan al televidente en las redes de esta formidable novela.

programme.title: Episodio 11
programme.desc: Nene trata de disculparse con Eva, pero no consigue mediar palabra. Ella esta muy alterada y decide echarlo de la casa tirandole la ropa en la cara, como este no se retira ella le pega donde mas le duele, rompiendole sus trofeos. Asi logra sacarlo de la habitacion. Santiago pierde la nocion del tiempo cuando enfrenta a Micaela y todos a su alrededor se pierden ante su belleza, lo mismo le pasa a ella. No dejan pasar la oportunidad de mirarse uno al otro. Carolina le cuenta a su amiga la aventura que tuvo en el bano con su cirujano, en plena charla llega Renata y presenta Daniel como su esposo, noticia que deja perpleja a Carolina.

programme.title: Episodio 116
programme.desc: Octavio se da cuenta que solo el sabe del paradero de Natalia, y puede sacar provecho de eso con decirle a Adolfo, Valerio o Luis Manuel, y ellos le pagaran muy bien por esa informacion, pero Tirsa le prohibe a Octavio llevarse a Natalia. Natalia recuerda haberse visto con un hombre antes y comienza a pensar que quiza ese hombre sea el padre del hijo que espera, en vez de serlo su esposo. Mientras tanto, Estefania, la prima de Luis Manuel lo distrae un poco y trata de lograr que se enamore de ella. Patricia y Diego llevan a cabo el plan de hacerlo pasar por su hermano Bruno ante sus conocidos, y nadie nota que en verdad no es el. Pasionaria declara que Bruno la beso en la playa, pero nadie le cree.

programme.title: Soros
programme.desc: Billionaire activist George Soros is one of the most influential and controversial figures of our time. He is maligned by ideologues on both the left and the right for daring to tackle the world’s problems. With unprecedented access to the man and his inner circle, director Jesse Dylan follows Soros and pulls back the curtain on his personal history, private wealth, and public activism.

programme.title: Hitler's Last Days
programme.desc: This is a fascinating documentary that gives insight into the last days of Hitler’s life as well as his death. With expert contributors like Guy Walters and Dr. Lisa Pine, this project uncovers an intriguing perspective on history.

programme.title: The Real Oppenheimer
programme.desc: In 1945, the world was ushered into the atomic age. With his role as the Father of the Bomb solidified, Oppenheimer became increasingly worried about the potential danger that scientific inventions could pose to humanity.

programme.title: Meghan Markle: American Duchess
programme.desc: Meghan's rise to the top of British society revealed some deep- seated issues in a multicultural country. How did the most adored woman in the world become the subject of such vicious tabloid gossip?

programme.title: Meghan Markle: Changing Traditions
programme.desc: She’s here, she’s royal and she’s shaking things up. Meghan Markle has now become very much part of the most famous family in the world, but this strong and powerful woman is not stopping there.

programme.title: Meghan Markle: Unforgiven
programme.desc: Drama, controversy, reconciliation. Meghan Markle was thrown into the spotlight in 2017 after her whirlwind romance with Prince Harry took centre stage. Falling in and out of favour with the press and public alike, Meghan has proven to divide the opinions of royal followers around the world. This is her story.

programme.title: Harry & Meghan The Complete Story: The Meeting
programme.desc: Prince Harry and Meghan Markle, Duke and Duchess of Sussex, are the modern-day fairytale we deserve. From the first whispers of a possible romance between the former Suits actress and former bad-boy of Kensington Palace to a wedding straight out of a Disney cartoon, the royal power couple has captured hearts across the globe.

programme.title: Harry & Meghan The Complete Story: The Wedding
programme.desc: It hasn’t been all unicorns and rainbows for Harry and Meghan. The wedded couple have weathered so many storms and media scandals that you’d think they’ve been married for a decade, not a few short years. Through it all, Meghan has been the picture of grace and poise. And Harry has pushed back against every royal protocol set in stone to defend and support his wife.

programme.title: Harry & Meghan The Complete Story: The Goodbye
programme.desc: The decision was clear - duty or love? Will their decision to start a new life in America distance them in more than just miles from Harry's royal family Their new life in Hollywood has changed the course of royal history forever.

programme.title: The Diana Story: Part I: The Young Princess
programme.desc: From Diana’s first steps into the royal world to the birth of her two sons and heirs, this documentary tells the story of Diana's early years.

programme.title: The Diana Story: Part II: Broken Hearts
programme.desc: The marriage of Prince Charles and Princess Diana remains infamous for being one of the most turbulent royal weddings in modern history. As the cracks began to form the world watched. What should have been the fairytale couple could not hold any longer. Discover the truth of what really lead to the split, as the world behind palace gates is uncovered.

programme.title: The Diana Story: Part III: Legacy Of Love
programme.desc: A late night phone call from Paris brought news that would rock the world. The sudden and tragic death of Princess Diana devastated millions. Hear what it was really like to be at the eye of the storm, as Diana's closest friend and confidant shares his story of heartbreak and farewell.

programme.title: The Taylor Swift Story: Dare To Dream

programme.title: Selena Gomez: Devotion
programme.desc: After returning from her 5 year break from music, Selena Gomez has blown the world away with her 3rd studio album Rare. She has transformed over the years, from Disney pop star to award winning film and tv producer. She is one of the biggest stars in Hollywood and is certain one of the most devoted to her art.

programme.title: The Barbie Story
programme.desc: A documentary about the origins of Barbie and her worldwide impact.

programme.title: Beyonce: Queen B

programme.title: Justin Bieber: Rise to Fame
programme.desc: The Transformation from small town Canadian boy to international superstar happened almost overnight. Teen Idol delves into how the young star copes with fame and how he chooses to spend his limited free time. programme.title: The Last 24 Hours: John Lennon
programme.desc: On the morning of December 8, 1980 John Lennon was happy in New York and looking forward to the future. Having just turned 40 he had finally recovered from the years as a Beatle. But by the end of that day John would be dead and the world would be in mourning. Here are the final 24 hours of the ex-Beatle’s life before he was so senselessly murdered by Mark David Chapman."

programme.title: The Last 24 Hours: Prince
programme.desc: The world mourned the loss of one of it’s most innovative performers in April 2016. While Prince’s official autopsy confirmed that the singer died from an overdose of the painkiller fentanyl, investigators have still been looking to clear up some additional mysteries surrounding the case. We take a look into the last 24 hours of his death and look for the real answers as to what happened.

programme.title: The Last 24 Hours: Jimi Hendrix

programme.title: The Last 24 Hours: Michael Jackson
programme.desc: The ultimate king of pop Michael Jackson spent his last hours battling insomnia and pleading with his personal physician to give him a powerful anesthetic to combat his chronic sleeplessness according to a search-warrant affidavit. programme.desc: A prostitute tries to outrun the police during a foot chase. A man claims he can only meet women at motels since he lives with his mom. A prostitute fresh out of jail protests that he’s not trying to return to his old career.

programme.title: Tree Hugging
programme.desc: An ex-felon threatens to kill his spouse after she announces she want to divorce him. A driver is stopped with suspicious plants in her car. A woman crashes her friends truck into a pedestrian and a tree.

programme.title: Crawling to Vegas
programme.desc: A driver leads police on a slow speed chase towards Las Vegas. Three people are suspected of using contraband. A multi-neighbor dispute devolves into a fight involving guns and bats.

programme.title: First Do No Harm
programme.desc: A suicidal man tries to taunt police into shooting him. Undercover officers expose an illegal operation at a pain management clinic. A woman claims she’s just a bystander to a motorcycle hit and run.

programme.title: Safe Cracking
programme.desc: A man stages a sit-in in his car in an attempt to stop it from being towed. A homeowner denies that he’s selling drugs despite the large amount of evidence found in his home. A safe full of evidence is found during a traffic stop.

programme.title: High Jump Fail
programme.desc: A family with kids is taken on a high speed car chase. A intoxicated suspect tries to jump a fence while protesting that he’s not trying to run away. A jealous boyfriend terrorizes his girlfriend and her parents.

programme.title: Bumming a Smoke
programme.desc: A suspect tries to elude officers by driving on a rough road. An argument over a cigarette turns ugly. Kids throw rocks from an overpass at the wrong car.

programme.title: Neighborhood Rage
programme.desc: A suspect ditches his bike then tries to outrun the police. Neighbors fight about a road rage incident using rocks and a baseball bat. Suspects in a stopped car attempt to hide all the evidence against them.

programme.title: My Bills Won't Wait
programme.desc: A suspect calls the police and states that he wants to kill himself and any officer who tries to help him. None of the three occupants of a stopped car will admit to ownership of a bag of drugs. A man begs not to be arrested so that he can pay child support.

programme.title: Family Therapy
programme.desc: Officers are flagged down and alerted to a group of armed men assaulting people at a nearby home. A fight between a father and his adult son takes a dark turn. A father threatens his daughter and her boyfriend with a knife.

programme.title: Spiked but Still Moving
programme.desc: A suspect refuses to stop his vehicle even after the officers spike his tires. A dispute over money results in a pregnant woman being attacked. A woman asks for officers to help her rescue cats from a trailer.

programme.title: Nightvision
programme.desc: A man on a late-night bike ride is stopped by officers for not having a headlamp. A suspect in a domestic dispute admits to hitting a woman. A man doesn’t deal with being laughed at by his neighbor in a peaceful way.

programme.title: Now It's Lawn Furniture
programme.desc: A traffic stop over a broken brake light turns into a foot chase. A man handles bad news by throwing his furniture out of the window. A vehicle pursuit ends with a K-9 unit’s help.

programme.title: Don't Make her Angry
programme.desc: A man needs police assistance when his angry ex-girlfriend crawls through his window. Police must play hide-and-seek when they attempt to execute an arrest warrant. A man is threatened with violence when he refuses to turn his car’s headlights off.

programme.title: And Through the Woods
programme.desc: Officers chase a fleeing suspect as he runs through the woods and into a rose bush. An elderly man puts himself in the middle of a knife fight. Two brothers disagree over letting officers search their car.

programme.title: She Came Onto Me
programme.desc: An undercover police officer sets up a sting to buy drugs. Officers find a surprise in a suspect’s trunk. A man claims that a prostitute has kidnapped him.

programme.title: Read the Signs
programme.desc: Police follow a car after it leaves a drug house. A police officer in Las Vegas goes undercover posing as a ‘john.’ Officers give chase when they observe a car making an illegal U-Turn.

programme.title: Hitman for Hire
programme.desc: Police set up a undercover operation to bust a suspect who wants to hire a hit man to kill her husband. Unknown to her, the hit man she hired is an undercover police officer. The suspect denies doing anything wrong despite all of her crimes being caught on camera.

programme.title: You're Not Banksy
programme.desc: Officers get a tip and locate the suspect in a recent shooting. A woman is questioned when she is found parked alone in her car behind closed businesses. Officers respond to a call involving juveniles spray painting an electrical box.

programme.title: Sharp Knives and Dirty Donuts
programme.desc: A customer pulls out a knife when asked to leave the store. A man doing donuts in a motel parking lot is questioned about a love triangle. Officers are flagged down by a man who was shot at while riding his bike.

programme.title: No Shirt, Lots of Service
programme.desc: When approached by police, a suspect decides to take his shirt off and taunt the officers. Twin sisters ask for help when their third sister is threated by her boyfriend. An intoxicated suspect crashes his wife’s car into a light pole.

programme.title: You've Gotta Believe Me
programme.desc: A DWI suspect flees from police because he thinks they won’t believe his version of events. A suspect is stopped for jaywalking but when questioned she can’t keep still. A naive man leaves his car unattended for a moment.

programme.title: Poor Conflict Resolution
programme.desc: A suspect in a traffic stop decides to handle the situation by screaming at the police. Officers have a close encounter with a suspect who admits that he has hidden contraband. A man’s clothing choices tip police off to possible criminal behavior.

programme.title: Wearing My Crime
programme.desc: A suspect flees from police and attempts to hide contraband from them. A driver is pulled over and is literally covered in his crimes. An employee of a cell phone store attempts to scam the police and her employers.

programme.title: A Song of Fire and Cleaning
programme.desc: The pursuit of a criminal driver ends in a fire and police rescue. Police track down an elusive suspect. A family dispute over cleaning a garage ends with the police being called.

programme.title: Pour One Out
programme.desc: Rather than stop, a driver decides to lead police on a high-speed chase. A woman is shot at by her ‘sugar daddy.’ A fleeing suspect dumps a suspicious liquid out of his window.

programme.title: Naked and Tired
programme.desc: Officers are called when two intoxicated suspects decide to have some fun and vandalize a fence. Undercover officers set up a narcotics sting at a hotel. A man is found lying naked in a parking lot.

programme.title: Not Gonna Stop
programme.desc: Despite driving a large SUV and trailer, a suspect tries to outrun the police. A driver tries to hide contraband on his person. Police are called into a domestic dispute involving a husband and wife.

programme.title: All The World's Our Bedroom
programme.desc: Officers are called to remove a man sleeping in a parking spot at Wal-Mart. A free-spirited couple takes their relationship to their front lawn. A resident brings a knife to a meeting with his building property manager.

programme.title: Amnesia Can Happen
programme.desc: Police officers set up a sting operation using a taxi cab in to bust prostitution. A man claims he can’t remember his ‘girlfriend’s’ name when officers suspect the woman is actually a stranger. Female undercover officers set up a sting operation to bust johns.

programme.title: Two Mr. Fix Its
programme.desc: A suspect attempts to flee when officers tell him they will search him. Two men get in a fight over window installation. A hotel room is filled like a clown car with multiple suspects.

programme.title: Flipped Out
programme.desc: A suspect leads police on an extended pursuit throughout New Orleans. When he’s flipped off by his neighbors, a man responds by firing a gun. Police pull over a Porsche and discover it’s stolen.

programme.title: Make it a Large Soda
programme.desc: A motorcyclist refuses to stop for the police and later tries to escape on foot. A pedestrian is found to have a large soda cup full of anything but soda. A man calls for police help when he’s verbally attacked on a city bus.

programme.title: A Bag, a Bus and a Break In
programme.desc: A couple calls for help when a man breaks into their home. A school bus is involved in a hit and run accident. Officer find a one gallon bag of contraband in a suspect’s car.

programme.title: Sinning and Thieving
programme.desc: Officers break up a fight between a couple in the middle of the street. Not even a church is immune to being robbed. A dispute between neighbors involves deadly weapons.

programme.title: Shots in the Big Easy
programme.desc: In New Orleans, police respond to a shots fired call. A suspect peddles a bike on the wrong side of the road with his girlfriend on the handlebars. A woman reports her husband to the police when he throws her down the stairs.

programme.title: Time to Climb
programme.desc: A couple flees a routine traffic stop. An intoxicated woman climbs a tree. Construction workers are pulled over for a hand-to-hand transaction.

programme.title: Dine and Flee
programme.desc: A sting operation is set up to catch narcotics dealers. A man flees a restaurant without paying his four-hundred-dollar tab. A traffic stop for a tint violation leads to a felony arrest for narcotics.

programme.title: Gas up and Run!
programme.desc: A man is tasered twice after struggling with two deputies. A gas station fight ends in a foot chase. A deputy pulls over a pair of quarreling lovers after they run a stop sign.

programme.title: ' Time Capsule
programme.desc: As the Smurfs busily build a time capsule for all of their talents, Papa Smurf frantically tries to unravel an ancient Druid riddle before disaster strikes the forest.

programme.title: ' Springtime
programme.desc: The wicked wizard Gargamel asks the sorcerer Balthazar for a recipe to capture the Smurfs. It involves kidnapping Mother Nature to stop the arrival of Spring. Luckily, the Smurfs save the day.

programme.title: Handy's Sweetheart
programme.desc: Handy learns it’s better to have smurfed than not to have smurfed at all when he learns his true love is really a mermaid. Can they really live with each other forever?

programme.title: Foul Weather Smurf
programme.desc: Handy invents a weather machine that will allow the Smurfs to control their environment at will. Unfortunately, they cannot agree on whether it should rain or be sunny so the machine overloads and explodes.

programme.title: Hefty's Heart
programme.desc: Gargamel infects Hefty's heart with hate and then uses the little Smurf as a decoy for the others. Fortunately, Hefty's love overcomes his hate and he helps his little friends escape from Gargamel's clutches.

programme.title: Skyscraper Smurfs
programme.desc: Sure, a village of mushroom-shaped houses is nice and jolly... But not very modern, in Architect Smurf's view. What the Smurfs need is smurfdominium, a new, daring concept that will change the art of living forever...

programme.title: A Little Smurf Confidence
programme.desc: Papa Smurf gives Weakling a special cream to wear that will restore his strength. Shortly after, he is awarded for his daring deeds of strength and his confidence really soars when he realizes the cream is smurfberry jam.

programme.title: Calling Dr Smurf
programme.desc: As his name implies, Dabbler Smurf is incapable of staying put in any one activity. He goes from one pursuit to another with the greatest of ease and never finishes what he's begun. But suddenly here he is smitten by the love of the medical profession. Dabbler wants to become a doctor and all of the Smurfs, with Papa Smurf in the lead, are going to help him to achieve his wish.

programme.title: A Gift For Papa's Day
programme.desc: Gargamel steals Papa Smurf's birthday hat to lure the Smurfs into a trap. Papa tricks Gargamel into releasing them and then keeps the unusual hat to remind everyone of their great escape.

programme.title: Futuresmurfed
programme.desc: Balthazar the Enchanter is a man of vision. He knows that the times of alchemy are drawing to their end. The future belongs to those who will understand science...but how can he see into the future? Perhaps by kidnapping Father Time. The Smurfs will help to put things right after Little Thunder, a dinosaur, escapes through a gash in the fabric of time.

programme.title: Heart Of Gold
programme.desc: Whatever Brainy Smurf says, the Clockwork Smurf devised by Handy has feelings just like any normal blue Smurf. At least it seems to be so until Clockwork Smurf loses what Handy had fitted inside its ribcage: a heart of gold. When the evil wizard Gargamel and his apprentice Scruple find the tiny contraption and fit it with a heart of stone, the Smurfs are in for a bad time...

programme.title: Never Smurf Off Till Tomorrow
programme.desc: A fierce wind carries the Smurfs' windmill away, with several Smurfs inside. Is Lazy Smurf really at fault or is an injustice being committed? Are the captive Smurfs going to be saved from the volcano's crater? Is Brainy going to smurf up his mouth for a moment?

programme.title: Sassette
programme.desc: Snappy and Nat steal Gargamel's formula to make another Smurf – a female to be a companion to Smurfette. They create Sassette, who causes mischief wherever she goes. Papa uses his Smurfiness Solution to turn Gargamel's evil Sassette into a playful Smurfy Sassette.

programme.title: The Golden Smurf Award
programme.desc: Hogatha disguises herself as the Golden Smurf Award to catch the Smurfs in order to use them as the main ingredient in her beauty cream. Vanity convinces her to try his recipe and before long, the wicked sorceress is covered with mud and sent careening over the hills into Gargamel's house.

programme.title: Queen Smurfette
programme.desc: Smurfette becomes Queen for a day on her birthday. But this gets out of hand when Father Time falls asleep, neglecting to end the days. Tempers begin to flare among the Smurfs, who are tired of servitude. Papa rushes to wake Father Time and brings peace again to Smurfland.

programme.title: The Smurfs And The Money Tree
programme.desc: The wicked wizard Gargamel has come up with yet another diabolical plan with the help of his mother, who isn't much nicer than him. He wants to tempt the Smurfs with money of which they have no notion. Will Greedy take the bait?

programme.title: Speak For Yourself, Farmer Smurf
programme.desc: Farmer hides his love for Smurfette by assuming a disguise and sending her poems. When they finally meet, they are captured by Bigmouth and in their struggle to get free, they discover their mutual friendship.

programme.title: Smurf On The Run
programme.desc: Little things can sometimes bring about big effects. In trying to catch Sassette, Gargamel upsets the Balance of Truth, and from then on everybody in the world tells lies. Even Papa Smurf is changed into a pathological liar. What is more, the Spirit of the Scales chain Gargamel and Sassette to each other, and together they have to replace the Topaz of Truth....

programme.title: Tailor's Magic Needle
programme.desc: Tailor Smurf has to make an outfit for every Smurf before the Fall fashion show. Brainy Smurf wants to help him and, using Papa Smurf's book of Magic, he conjures up a magic needle that sews ten times faster than tailor... But is it really any good?

programme.title: Smurf On Wood
programme.desc: The evil wizard Gargamel once again meets Esmeralda, the gypsy fortune-teller, and she finds a novel way of getting the gold coin that Gargamel imprudently shows her. But the Smurfs in their turn are tricked into believing there is such a thing as a good-luck tree...

programme.title: Papa's Wedding Day
programme.desc: When the flower fairy Nymph arrives at the Smurf Village, all the Smurfs fall for her charm and wit. And soon they learn that she is to be some sort of Mama Smurf to them...

programme.title: Lure Of The Orb
programme.desc: Allura the Enchantress possesses a very special magic orb whose energy, as she says, can lift spirits and inspire the uninspired! All you have to do is hold the orb between your hands... It is true the orb bestows inspiration, up to a point. But its side effects can be very dangerous, as the Smurfs find out when they become addicted to it...

programme.title: Bubble, Bubble, Smurfs In Trouble
programme.desc: Each morning, dew is deposited by water sprites on forest leaves. Wait till you see what happens when Scaredy Smurf gets hold of the dew-making magic wand...

programme.title: Papa's Flying Bed
programme.desc: Gargamel casts a spell on Papa's new bed so anyone who sleeps in it is transported to the location of his dream. The drowsy Smurfs' fantasies lead them to a private ship, a castle and finally to Gargamel's. They escape when Clumsy falls asleep and dreams of home.

programme.title: Grouchy Makes A Splash
programme.desc: We all know Grouchy Smurf hates a lot of things. But one thing he hates more than anything else is water, when there is enough of it to drown in. You see, Grouchy can't swim. And when the Smurfs notice this peculiarity and try to teach him how to survive in water, the evil wizard Gargamel makes things a little more dangerous than they ought to be....

programme.title: Can't Smurf The Music
programme.desc: There is nothing the sorceress Chlorhydris hates so much as love in the world. She would like to see all love banished from the face of the Earth, and she's going to start with music. She puts a spell on a magic horn so that it will suck the music out of every song... especially the Smurfs' songs. Helped by their friend Laconia, the Smurfs may be able to resist Chlorhydris' evil plan...

programme.title: Lure Of The Orb
programme.desc: Allura the Enchantress possesses a very special magic orb whose energy, as she says, can lift spirits and inspire the uninspired! All you have to do is hold the orb between your hands... It is true the orb bestows inspiration, up to a point. But its side effects can be very dangerous, as the Smurfs find out when they become addicted to it...

programme.title: Smurfic Games
programme.desc: The Smurfs discover the spirit and joy of friendly competition when they hold their first "Smurfic Games". After a near miss with the troublesome cat Azrael, the Smurfs decide they need to get into better shape. Papa Smurf suggests that the Smurfs tone their bodies as well as sharpen their athletic abilities by inaugurating the "Smurfic Games".

programme.title: The Fountain Of Smurf
programme.desc: The Smurfs discover a fountain of youth that is guarded by a wicked troll, who steals Papa Smurf's magic book. They convince Gargamel to help them and the greedy villain runs to get the water, but manages to fall in with the troll. As the two chase each other all over the countryside, the Smurfs are able to retrieve Papa Smurf's book.

programme.title: The Abominable Snowbeast
programme.desc: Brainy and his friends organize a journey to Ice Mountain to pick the rare snow flower for Papa Smurf. They meet a terrifying snow beast that befriends them, due to Smurfette's kindness, and helps them find the tiny flower.

programme.title: The Trojan Smurf
programme.desc: Gargamel, the evil wizard, has devised a new plan to capture the Smurfs: he builds a giant statue in the shape of Papa Smurf. Thus, he hopes, the Smurfs are going to drag the statue into their Village.

programme.title: Unsound Smurf
programme.desc: In an effort to give Papa some quiet time, Brainy uses one of Papa's spells to create a magical sound barrier around the village. Papa cannot reverse the spell and sends the Smurflings, who are trapped outside the Village, to a noisemaker. Baby takes a bottle of sound from the noisemaker, which breaks the barrier.

programme.title: Smurf Box Derby
programme.desc: Handy Smurf makes another invention: the Smurfmobile. Each Smurf has his – or her – customized vehicle and all, or almost all, the Smurfs enjoy a little spin... But then the evil wizard Gargamel gets hold of the idea and starts making trouble for the Smurfs...

programme.title: The Bad Place
programme.desc: What is this little moon coming from above? Why, it's a crater-pockmarked globe of mud inhabited by the Grimeys, a family of mud-splattering, mud-eating creatures from out there in the sky. Not all the Smurfs are enthusiastic about the visitors....

programme.title: Bigmouth's Friend
programme.desc: Gargamel and Balthazar command a giant robot to force King Gerard to hand over Clockwork Smurf. When the robot is about to destroy the castle, Clockwork's new, large, and awkward friend Bigmouth defeats the robot. Clockwork is hurt in the battle but Handy fixes him and implants a voice box so he can say "Hi"!

programme.title: Crooner Smurf
programme.desc: Harmony Smurf is no longer wanted in the Smurf Choir: his singing is too far off-key. But Papa Smurf gives him an amulet that will make him a vocal virtuoso. Now here comes Hogatha...

programme.title: He Who Smurfs Last
programme.desc: Jokey's practical jokes go too far when Chlorhydris is the victim of one. She gets her revenge on the Smurfs by creating a spell to steal their sense of humor. Grouchy, who had no sense of humor to begin with, breaks the spell by getting back the humor potion.

programme.title: Sassette
programme.desc: Snappy and Nat steal Gargamel's formula to make another Smurf – a female to be a companion to Smurfette. They create Sassette, who causes mischief wherever she goes. Papa uses his Smurfiness Solution to turn Gargamel's evil Sassette into a playful Smurfy Sassette.

programme.title: Every Picture Smurfs A Story
programme.desc: The evil Maestro's magical paints have the power to transport his models onto canvas – forever! Papa Smurf directs Painter to switch his paints and before long, Maestro is enshrined in a picture next to his dream girl, Smurfette.

programme.title: The Master Smurf
programme.desc: There is an evil power in the Titan's crown that Miner Smurf finds underground. And Greedy Smurf is the Smurf to fall victim to it. Then Gargamel comes up with some new schemes to destroy the Smurfs, and everything gets hopelessly tangled.

programme.title: Have You Smurfed Your Pet Today?
programme.desc: The Smurfs get so involved with Handy's new toy that they forget to feed Puppy. Gargamel lures Puppy into a cage with food and holds him for ransom – the Smurfs' magic secrets. The Smurflings distract Gargamel with the toy long enough to rescue Puppy and they vow to never neglect him again.

programme.title: Papa's Worrywarts
programme.desc: Papa Smurf's worries make him break into a rash of worrywarts. The only way to relieve him of his bout of indecision-inducing disease is to have him rub the horn of a Wartmonger, a sloppy, slimy, stupid and brutal enemy of the Pussywillow Pixies...

programme.title: A Hovel Is Not A Home
programme.desc: In his search for a grander hovel, Gargamel looks in the Great Book of Spells to conjure up a new home. But all of his spells backfire and that convinces him that there's no place like home!

programme.title: Jokey's Joke Book
programme.desc: Jokey Smurf's joke boxes are no longer funny to the other Smurfs. Jokey finds new ideas in his Great Joke Book, but these ideas are even less popular in the Village. And here comes the evil Gargamel with a few jokes of his own...

programme.title: Essence Of Brainy
programme.desc: Brainy Smurf is not the same anymore. He is polite, considerate, modest and calls every other Smurf Sir or Madame. All the Smurfs are worried that Brainy has lost all that makes his personality. They ought to be worried, for Brainy has been the victim of a system called an Essence Remover that Scruple, Gargamel's apprentice, uses... But Brainy's essence is coming back!

programme.title: Never Smurf Off Till Tomorrow
programme.desc: A fierce wind carries the Smurfs' windmill away, with several Smurfs inside. Is Lazy Smurf really at fault or is an injustice being committed? Are the captive Smurfs going to be saved from the volcano's crater? Is Brainy going to smurf up his mouth for a moment?

programme.title: Smurf On Wood
programme.desc: The evil wizard Gargamel once again meets Esmeralda, the gypsy fortune-teller, and she finds a novel way of getting the gold coin that Gargamel imprudently shows her. But the Smurfs in their turn are tricked into believing there is such a thing as a good-luck tree...

programme.title: Papa's Wedding Day
programme.desc: When the flower fairy Nymph arrives at the Smurf Village, all the Smurfs fall for her charm and wit. And soon they learn that she is to be some sort of Mama Smurf to them...

programme.title: The Whole Smurf And Nothing But The Smurf
programme.desc: The evil wizard Gargamel is able to capture the Smurfette. Now he is going to give her a truth serum and know all of Papa Smurf' secrets... But then Gargamel makes a big mistake and gives the Smurfette a fib formula!

programme.title: The Gallant Smurf
programme.desc: Queen Felicity will not let her son, Prince Godfrey, marry his sweetheart Pricilla. What she wants as a daughter-in-law is a girl who shows her something she's never seen before. When Hogatha learns of this, and also discovers the existence of Grandpa Smurf, she feels confident that she can surprise the Queen with her capture. Of course, Hogatha must first capture Grandpa Smurf...

programme.title: Speak For Yourself, Farmer Smurf
programme.desc: Farmer hides his love for Smurfette by assuming a disguise and sending her poems. When they finally meet, they are captured by Bigmouth and in their struggle to get free, they discover their mutual friendship.

programme.title: Chip Off The Old Smurf
programme.desc: Disaster strikes when Brainy and Baby mix up Papa Smurf's formulas, leaving them powerless before an army of hungry locusts unleashed on the forest by Gargamel.

programme.title: The Comet Is Coming!
programme.desc: Papa's note to the Smurfs about viewing a comet is delivered torn. The Smurfs read only the first part and think their world is coming to an end. They plan how to spend their last day until Papa returns to clear up the misunderstanding and assure them that they are safe.

programme.title: Lazy's Nightmare
programme.desc: Every time Lazy falls asleep, he is caught in the same recurrent nightmare: he is in the power of Morphio, an evil sorcerer who wants to capture as many sleeping souls as possible. One after another, all the Smurfs are going to fall in Morphio's clutches. All of them? Well, maybe not, if Papa Smurf can help it. And Papa Smurf goes to the Sandman for help...

programme.title: A Loss Of Smurfs
programme.desc: When the emergency call rings, all the Smurfs in the Village drop what they are doing and run to hear the news. But when Vanity Smurf calls for an assembly so that the Smurfs can admire his new hat, it is too much. They send him on his way out of the village, and Vanity has the bad luck of meeting Lofty, the Elf, who suggests a horrible mud bath...

programme.title: The Smurfs And The Money Tree
programme.desc: The wicked wizard Gargamel has come up with yet another diabolical plan with the help of his mother, who isn't much nicer than him. He wants to tempt the Smurfs with money of which they have no notion. Will Greedy take the bait?

programme.title: Gargamel's Giant
programme.desc: The evil wizard Gargamel wants to create a monster. A horrible, gigantic creature, an awesome being that is going to destroy all the Smurfs! But Gargamel makes a slight mistake, and the result is going to astonish him and his cat Azrael.

programme.title: The Fake Smurf
programme.desc: Hogatha turns herself into a Smurf, plotting revenge on the little people for destroying her magic locket. Papa Smurf outwits her and banishes her from the forest once more.

programme.title: All The Smurf's A Stage
programme.desc: Poet Smurf's new play is going to be his greatest work ever, and it will feature the most favourite Smurf of all: Smurfette in the leading female role. All the other Smurfs vie for the honour of playing opposite Smurfette. Even Timid Smurf, who is the shy and retiring type, is a candidate for the part. Brainy Smurf, self-appointed manager of the play, does not see it that way...

programme.title: The Smurf Who Would Be King
programme.desc: Dreamy yearns to be King after reading a story about them. He falls through a whirlpool while on his ship and finds himself in the land of pokies who think Dreamy is their long-lost King. When he confronts the pokies' enemies, the Norfnags, he finds they aren't fearful at all. Dreamy bumps his head and wakes up to discover it was just a dream, yet finds a jewel in his cap, just like the ones the pokies mine for a living.

programme.title: Master Scruple
programme.desc: Farmer Smurf is the reluctant master of a genie named Gourdy, whose enthusiasm for service is somewhat excessive. After yet another incident due to Gourdy's overzealousness, Farmer Smurf says something he shouldn't and Gourdy disappears. And guess who finds him? Well, it's Scruple, apprentice to the evil wizard Gargamel. And who should steal Gourdy from Scruple, if not Gargamel himself?

programme.title: Alarming Smurfs
programme.desc: Feeling unwanted, the Smurflings run away. They take things to remind them of home, so the Smurfs think there's a thief in their midst. Brainy tries to catch the thief by installing smurfler alarms. The alarms cause a ruckus that draws the Smurflings home, where Papa tells them they are wanted.

programme.title: Smurfiplication
programme.desc: The evil wizard Gargamel creates a magic formula that duplicates everything it touches. And surprise! Suddenly there are six Brainy Smurf! This creates a few interesting situations in the Village... And also at Gargamel's!

programme.title: Sir Hefty
programme.desc: Sir Hefty discovers a wayward knight to help him defeat a dragon whose fire is threatening to destroy the forest. Alas, the knight proves to be a coward, leaving Hefty to prove just how brave he is when he sends the dragon away from Smurf Village.

programme.title: The Lost City Of Yore
programme.desc: Curiosity brings Nosey Smurf to the lair of the Hag Sisters, who want to find the terrifying Sceptre of Yore... And Gargamel wants to cheat the two witches as he tries to destroy the Smurfs.

programme.title: The Incredible Shrinking Wizard
programme.desc: Gargamel has thrown in his slime pond so much poisonous muck that the water becomes enchanted and Gargamel, after falling in, suddenly finds himself much smaller that he would wish. Actually he is going to be so small that Papa Smurf will save him!

programme.title: Snappy's Way
programme.desc: Did you know that if you catch a troll, he may grant you one wish? It just happens that Aloysius the Troll gets caught in one of Gargamel's Smurf traps. Snappy Smurf sets him free and as a reward, gets to make all other Smurfs obey his every whim. Now this brings a lot of trouble to the Smurfs, as Smurflings, sometimes, ask for things that are not good for them... or anybody else.

programme.title: Reckless Smurfs
programme.desc: This time, Gargamel's plan cannot fail. Undeterred by Azrael's derisive cackling, the evil wizard perfects a magic substance called Daredevil Dust, which is going to change all the Smurfs into rash, incautious swashbucklers. Will Papa Smurf fall into Gargamel's trap? Will their enemy catch all the Smurfs? Will this story have a happy ending?

programme.title: The Winged Wizard
programme.desc: Determined to fly over Smurf village to catch a Smurf to take to the Wizard's Convention, Gargamel invokes his Book of Spells to help him. A series of funny flying machine mishaps occur and Gargamel is once more the laughing stock of the Wizard's Convention.

programme.title: Smurf Box Derby
programme.desc: Handy Smurf makes another invention: the Smurfmobile. Each Smurf has his – or her – customized vehicle and all, or almost all, the Smurfs enjoy a little spin... But then the evil wizard Gargamel gets hold of the idea and starts making trouble for the Smurfs...

programme.title: Spelunking Smurfs
programme.desc: The starving Smurfs discover a cave that has a stash of frozen food inside guarded by an equally frozen troll who was imprisoned because of his greed by a magic diamond. As the Smurfs defrost the cave, Gargamel steals the food, but the magic diamond transforms him into an icy mass and the freed troll happily helps the Smurfs carry the food back to their village.

programme.title: Lure Of The Orb
programme.desc: Allura the Enchantress possesses a very special magic orb whose energy, as she says, can lift spirits and inspire the uninspired! All you have to do is hold the orb between your hands... It is true the orb bestows inspiration, up to a point. But its side effects can be very dangerous, as the Smurfs find out when they become addicted to it...

programme.title: Handy's Sweetheart
programme.desc: Handy learns it’s better to have smurfed than not to have smurfed at all when he learns his true love is really a mermaid. Can they really live with each other forever?

programme.title: Smurfily Ever After
programme.desc: The boy from the wood and Laconia, the deaf-mute elf, ask Papa Smurf to celebrate their wedding. The Smurfs are getting the party ready, following the advice of the Smurfette, when Gargamel comes to put a spoke in their wheel.

programme.title: Put Upon Puppy
programme.desc: Life in the Smurf Village might be more peaceful if Puppy's behavior were a little more considerate. But the little Smurf dog is digging up Smurfette's flowers, dirtying Vanity's new wallpaper or ruining Papa Smurf's experiments. Yet Puppy's going to help the Smurfs out of a trap contrived by Gargamel... Or maybe he won't be disciplined enough...

programme.title: All Creatures Great And Smurf
programme.desc: Nat Smurf is convinced he can help all creatures with his healing ways, even the wicked Azrael after he gets his paw caught in a trap. He heals well, but even though he is tempted to stay with the Smurfs, he runs back to Gargamel while leading his old master away from Smurf Village.

programme.title: The Man In The Moon
programme.desc: Sick and tired of not being appreciated, the Man in the Moon quits his job and retires on Earth, to the Village of the Smurfs. The absence of a First Quarter Moon wreaks havoc in the customs of the Smurfs, and Mother Nature and Father Time get dragged in...

programme.title: Hefty And The Wheelsmurfer
programme.desc: Hefty Smurf learns what is to be handicapped when he breaks his leg. Handy Smurf creates the wheelsmurfer for him, a contraption that will give Hefty some mobility. But suddenly the evil wizard Gargamel appears on the scene.

programme.title: Baby's First Christmas
programme.desc: The wonderful joy of Christmas for Baby Smurf and everyone else is almost ruined by the evil Chlorhydris who puts a spell on Mr. Nicholas to stop him from spreading holiday cheer. Fortunately, Papa Smurf and his little blue creatures break the spell and Christmas spreads over the land once more.

programme.title: The Littlest Giant
programme.desc: Simon is lost in the forest and in search of his parents. Simon is the son of a couple of giants. The Smurfs try to bring him home, but then Gargamel interrupts the party.

programme.title: The Comet Is Coming!
programme.desc: Papa's note to the Smurfs about viewing a comet is delivered torn. The Smurfs read only the first part and think their world is coming to an end. They plan how to spend their last day until Papa returns to clear up the misunderstanding and assure them that they are safe.

programme.title: All The News That's Fit To Smurf
programme.desc: Curious Smurf has an idea: why not print a sheet with all the Village news? He's sure to interest all his readers of the Smurf Tattler. But things don't go exactly to plan when Papa finds super smurfberries.

programme.title: Smurfing For Gold
programme.desc: Gargamel the evil wizard is in trouble again. If he can't find an enormous amount of gold by sundown, all his possessions will be taken away from him. But the Smurfs are going to help their arch-enemy... Up to a point.

programme.title: To Smurf A Thief
programme.desc: The Smurfs and Homnibus befriend an unfortunate boy who is forced to steal for his master. Soon, the evil thief is turned over to the magistrate and the boy is happy to live with Homnibus.

programme.title: The Kaplowey Scroll
programme.desc: There is a terrifying magic word. When you direct the word at something or someone, you make it vanish into nothingness! Can the Smurfs undo its evil power before Gargamel gets hold of it?

programme.title: The Gallant Smurf
programme.desc: Queen Felicity will not let her son, Prince Godfrey, marry his sweetheart Pricilla. What she wants as a daughter-in-law is a girl who shows her something she's never seen before. When Hogatha learns of this, and also discovers the existence of Grandpa Smurf, she feels confident that she can surprise the Queen with her capture. Of course, Hogatha must first capture Grandpa Smurf...

programme.title: The Sky Is Smurfing
programme.desc: Scaredy Smurf runs into the Village screaming about the sky being about to smurf down. And just at the same moment, Papa Smurf is beset by uncontrollable fits of sneezing...

programme.title: Tattle-Tail Smurfs
programme.desc: Brainy Smurf's had enough. The Smurflings and Sassette keep on telling tales about him with unpleasant results. He therefore concocts a magic formula, taken from Papa Smurf's books of spells, which makes the little Smurfs' tails grow longer and longer every time they tell tales. What he hasn't counted on is that Gargamel now has a way of catching the Smurflings.

programme.title: Now You Smurf 'Em, Now You Don't
programme.desc: The underground trolls who want them to be their slaves capture the Smurfs. Papa Smurf ingeniously frees them and then destroys the trolls' magic crystal ball that gives them power over the Smurfs.

programme.title: Handy's Sweetheart
programme.desc: Handy learns it’s better to have smurfed than not to have smurfed at all when he learns his true love is really a mermaid. Can they really live with each other forever?

programme.title: Smurfette's Dancing Shoes
programme.desc: An evil imp gives Smurfette dancing shoes and then tricks her into promising to marry him. All her little friends rush to her rescue and Papa Smurf magically puts the dancing shoes on the imp. He is forced to dance off into the night.

programme.title: The Pussywillow Pixies
programme.desc: Clumsy Smurf's misadventures take him across a river into Pussywillow Hollow. There he meets the Pixies – charming and shapely beings whose enemies, the Wartmongers, will meet the Smurfs in some unforeseen ways.

programme.title: The Whole Smurf And Nothing But The Smurf
programme.desc: The evil wizard Gargamel is able to capture the Smurfette. Now he is going to give her a truth serum and know all of Papa Smurf' secrets... But then Gargamel makes a big mistake and gives the Smurfette a fib formula!

programme.title: Unsound Smurf
programme.desc: In an effort to give Papa some quiet time, Brainy uses one of Papa's spells to create a magical sound barrier around the village. Papa cannot reverse the spell and sends the Smurflings, who are trapped outside the Village, to a noisemaker. Baby takes a bottle of sound from the noisemaker, which breaks the barrier.

programme.title: Spelunking Smurfs
programme.desc: The starving Smurfs discover a cave that has a stash of frozen food inside guarded by an equally frozen troll who was imprisoned because of his greed by a magic diamond. As the Smurfs defrost the cave, Gargamel steals the food, but the magic diamond transforms him into an icy mass and the freed troll happily helps the Smurfs carry the food back to their village.

programme.title: Poet's Writers' Block
programme.desc: The Smurfs want a poem written for each of them. The pressure overwhelms Poet, so he runs away seeking inspiration. The Wilybeast King captures Poet and forces him to write a poem to cheer up the King's daughter. Poet learns that motivation must come from the heart and cannot be forced.

programme.title: The Chief Record Smurf
programme.desc: Due to a wild experiment Clumsy is able to store endless knowledge into his memory. Gargamel captures him, trying to unlock Papa Smurf's invisibility formula, but at the last minute, Clumsy tricks him with the wrong ingredients.

programme.title: Greedy Goes On Strike
programme.desc: Get up early in the morning, before any other Smurf is out of bed, to prepare a scrumptious Smurfberry muffin. Spend all morning on preparing Smurf delicacies for lunch. Than all afternoon to have dinner ready – and delicious – on time. And do you get so much as a thank you form the Smurfs? So Greedy Smurf quits. The Village is in trouble... And soon, so is Greedy.

programme.title: A Clockwork Smurf
programme.desc: Handy has built a very complex Smurf machine that does everything. It proves dangerous when it nearly destroys the village, but comes in useful when, with the help of the other Smurfs, it saves the young prince Gerard's kingdom from the queen aunt Imperia's dastardly intentions.

programme.title: The Last Smurfberry
programme.desc: Papa Smurf organizes a crew to sail to Smurfberry Island because Gargamel has killed all of the trees except one to trap the Smurfs. Gargamel follows them, but once more fails to catch them because the Witch of Smurfberry Island sends her nose-eating seagulls after them.

programme.title: Don Smurfo
programme.desc: Everyone has their own dreams. That of Smurfette is to meet the legendary Don Smurfo, the dashing, witty, swashbuckling hero of many an engrossing tale. The Smurfs shrug at this infatuation. But when a real-life Don Smurfo appears in the village and Smurfette snubs them all in favor of the bragging stranger, they take the matter a little more seriously.

programme.title: The Mr Smurf Contest
programme.desc: When Papa decides to throw a Harvest Moon ball, all the male Smurfs compete in a "Mr Smurf" contest for the honor of escorting Sassette. Gargamel sneaks into the contest after shrinking himself with blue dye, in the hope of capturing all the Smurfs when he returns to normal size. The Smurfs kick him out and Sassette lets Papa escort her.

programme.title: Hats Off To Smurf
programme.desc: In his search for something new, Vanity dons a Gargamel-made magic hat that transforms his face into a mess. Through trickery, Papa Smurf gets the antidote from the wicked wizard and once more, Vanity is beautiful.

programme.title: Lazy's Slumber Party
programme.desc: Poor Lazy! All he wants is a good night's rest. But no, all the Smurfs throw a party for him and, what's more, he gets dragged into a silly argument about painting giant Bigmouth's toes a bright tangerine red... It's a long, sleepless night for poor Lazy Smurf!

programme.title: A Clockwork Smurf
programme.desc: Handy has built a very complex Smurf machine that does everything. It proves dangerous when it nearly destroys the village, but comes in useful when, with the help of the other Smurfs, it saves the young prince Gerard's kingdom from the queen aunt Imperia's dastardly intentions.

programme.title: ' Time Capsule
